text:
Roughly 100 people are sleeping around the spiraling Interstate 80 ramps at University Avenue in Berkeley, the city’s mayor said Sunday, hours after crews blocked traffic to clear tons of detritus.

via @RachelSwan: https://t.co/RucsFOMopm

name: sfchronicle
text:
Authorities are investigating the death of an inmate who was found Saturday evening with a bedsheet around his neck at the West County Detention Facility in Richmond.
Story by @RachelSwan: https://t.co/NGmor2pDU0 https://t.co/alL5gp5B1J

text: RT @SportingGreenSF: The @49ers had six wide receivers in uniform Sunday, but Dante Pettis wasn’t among them. It was the latest bit of evidence that Pettis won’t realize the lofty expectations the 49ers had for him two years ago, writes @Eric_Branch  https://t.co/FtO8dUwOYZ
